  "market_context": "Following a Friday reversal with higher time frame bullish bias, Monday and Tuesday were combined into a single candle due to a bank holiday. This combined candle ran the prior swing low, opposing the anticipated higher bias without forming a valid reversal closure.",
  "key_observation": "Monday-Tuesday opposed the higher bias by running the low but did not produce a candle-2 closure; Wednesday then formed the candle-2 closure with failure swings on the high and high resistance liquidity on the low, signaling a midweek reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified higher time frame bias as bullish following a Friday reversal, with target liquidity above (previous daily high).",
    "Step 2: Observed Monday-Tuesday combined into one candle due to bank holiday, running the prior swing low but not closing back as a candle-2 closure — required waiting another day.",
    "Step 3: Wednesday produced a candle-2 closure in line with higher time frame bias, with failure swings on the high and high resistance liquidity on the low.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the hourly time frame to confirm a change in the state of delivery (CISD) and identified an SMT divergence off the low.",
    "Step 5: Anticipated this weekly/daily low was formed and looked for continuation higher targeting the previous daily high at ~20,205.",
    "Step 6: Price ran through a first minor target with no reaction, confirming continuation higher toward the previous daily high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded higher Thursday-Friday toward the previous daily high target at ~20,205, validating the midweek reversal continuation.",
  "lessons": "When Monday-Tuesday oppose the weekly bias without a valid candle-2 closure, wait for the next day. A Wednesday candle-2 closure with hourly CISD and SMT confirms a midweek reversal — trade continuation toward the previous daily high.",
